    <!-- Instruction Modal -->
    <div id="iModal" class="modal hide fade">
    <div class="modal-header">
    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">×</button>
    <h3 id="myModalLabel">Instructions</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-body">
    <h4>Create Petri Net</h4>
    <p>To <b>create a new petri net</b> simply click on the "Create new Petri Net" located on the home page.</p> 
    <h4>Controls</h4>
    <p>Once a petri net is created, you can add <b>places</b> and <b>transitions</b> to it by clicking their respective buttons. Once a place is created you can move it around simply by clicking and dragging it.</p>
    <p>To create an <b>arc</b> connection, drag the circle in the top right of a place or transistion over the place or transition you wish to connect. A transition can only connect to a place and vise versa. Note: the order in which you drag the arc determins the direction of the arc. </p>
    <p>To <b>delete</b> any item of the petri graph click the red circle. Don't worry you will be asked to confirm incase you accidentally misclick</p>
    <p>Finally to add <b>Tokens</b> to a place, single click the place you desire to add a token to. To fire a transition, single click the transition you want to fire. A transition will only fire if all of it's inputs have tokens</p>
    </div>    
    <div class="modal-footer">
    <button class="btn" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Close</button>
    </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
